# T1059.003 - Command and Scripting Interpreter: Windows Command Shell

**MITRE ATT&CK Technique:** [T1059.003](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/003/)

**Tactic:** Execution

**Objective:** Execute commands using cmd.exe to simulate attacker use of the Windows Command Shell for living-off-the-land techniques.

## Attack Attempts Summary

### 1. Attempt from Kali Linux (Remote Execution via SSH)
**Tools tried:**
- Custom batch file (`cmd-demo.bat`)
- Linux launcher script (`run-cmd-execution.sh`) using SCP + SSH

**Issues Encountered:**
- `Connection reset by peer` on port 22
- SSH session dropped immediately after handshake

**Troubleshooting Done:**
- Multiple restarts of sshd/ssh-agent services
- Re-installed OpenSSH.Server capability
- Configured DefaultShell registry key
- Fixed folder permissions
- Verified port 22 listening status
- Rebooted Windows 10 multiple times

**Result:** Failed. Remote cmd.exe execution via SSH was unreliable due to persistent OpenSSH connection issues.

### 2. Successful Method: Atomic Red Team (Local Execution)

**Command Used:**
```powershell
# Run all tests for T1059.003
Invoke-AtomicTest T1059.003
